headlines.description: Nat Dixon and Makinde London each scored 21 points and London grabbed a career-high 19 rebounds as short-handed Chattanooga picked up its first Southern Conference victory in its first eight starts, dropping Samford, 78-71 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chattanooga gets 1st SoCon win, powers past Samford, 78-71

headlines.description: Marvin Smith scored 13 points and his 3-point shot midway through the second half kicked off a 17-1 run that spurred UNC Greensboro to a 71-61 come-from-behind defeat of Furman Wednesday night and give coach Wes Miller his 100th career win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith, Alonso spark UNCG past Furman 71-61 in Southern tilt

headlines.description: Trae Bell-Haynes scored 21 points with five rebounds and Vermont extended its win streak to 10 with a 61-50 victory over Albany on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vermont extends streak to 10 with 61-50 win over Albany

headlines.description: Joe Sherburne scored 18 points, including a dagger of a 3-pointer from the corner to blunt a comeback and Maryland-Baltimore County defeated Binghamton 69-57 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sherburne helps UMBC hold off Binghamton 69-57

headlines.description: JD Notae and Devon Harris scored 21 points apiece and Jacksonville pulled away in the second half to beat Stetson 76-69 on Wednesday night for its fifth straight win in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacksonville beats Stetson 76-69 behind Notae, Harris

headlines.description: Ahmad Thomas scored 25 points, Raekwon Miller had 15 points, seven rebounds and eight assists and UNC Asheville beat Gardner-Webb 65-60 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas scores 25, UNC Asheville beats Gardner-Webb 65-60

headlines.description: Rob Marberry had 24 points on 10-of-12 shooting and eight rebounds, Kenny Cooper added 16 points and Lipscomb beat USC Upstate 92-78 on Wednesday night.
Tre Gray scored 20 points with five 3-pointers and Texas A&M-Corpus Christi never trailed in its 80-66 win over Abilene Christian on Wednesday night to end a three-game skid.
Jordan Howard scored a career-best 43 points and grabbed seven rebounds as Central Arkansas beat Stephen F. Austin 100-92 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Howard scores 43, Cent. Arkansas beats S.F. Austin 100-92

headlines.description: Jalon Gates scored 23 points, David Caraher and Braxton Bonds poured in 22 apiece and Houston Baptist led for all but six minutes to defeat Incarnate Word 102-86 in a meeting of the Southland Conference's winless teams Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Houston Baptist defeats Incarnate Word 102-86 in Southland

headlines.description: Roddy Peters and Tevon Saddler combined to score 50 points and Nicholls took over first-place in the Southland Conference after turning away Lamar, 79-74 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southland Conference leader Nicholls rolls past Lamar, 79-74

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
